 and ethnic minorities, immigrants and refugees. Among the issues addressed are primary prevention programs that target adolescents and young adults, strategies designed to engage men and boys, IPV screening in different settings, the impact of the criminalization of IPV on minority populations, restorative justice programs, interventions for women who use violence, and innovative shelter programming to prevent re-victimization. The volume concludes by identifying the gaps in knowledge about effective prevention and highlighting the most promising future directions for prevention research and strategies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aIntimate partner violencexPrevention. 7aFAMILY & RELATIONSHIPS / Abuse / Domestic Partner Abuse.2bisacsh1 aBanyard, Victoria L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoker, Ann L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoker, Ann, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCudmore, Rebecca M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCuevas, Carlos A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDasgupta, Shamita Das, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDecker, Michele R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFleet, Diane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFollingstad, Diane R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFollingstad, Diane, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGlass, Nancy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoodmark, Leigh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLarance, Lisa Y., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/r